  <li>For my 3 followers :-) who want to create images with  emojis with ruby :-).</li>
  <li>Sadly copying and pasting the emoji doesnâ€™t work.</li>
  <li>Neither does specifying the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Noto Color Emoji</code> font (imagemagick fails with â€œcannot read fontâ€).</li>
  <li>But oddly, copying and pasting an emoji into the command line e.g. <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">magick</code> or <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">convert</code> work with copy/pasted emojis.</li>
  <li>Finally, I could not get the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">rmagick/imagemagick</code> combo to work without using <a href="https://www.imagemagick.org/Usage/text/#pango">pango</a></li>
</ul>

